Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: attributeLastName

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: attributeCountry

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: attributeIPAddress

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: key
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined string that uniquely identifies the user. If the client app does not define a key, the SDK will assign an identifier associated with the anonymous user. The key cannot be made private.

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: secondary
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: The secondary key for the user. See the documentation for more information on it’s use for percentage rollout bucketing.

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: name
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined name for the user. (Default: nil)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: firstName
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined first name for the user. (Default: nil)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: lastName
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined last name for the user. (Default: nil)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: country
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined country for the user. (Default: nil)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: ipAddress
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined ipAddress for the user. (Default: nil)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: email
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined email address for the user. (Default: nil)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: avatar
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined avatar for the user. (Default: nil)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: custom
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined dictionary for the user. The client app may declare top level dictionary items as private. If the client app defines custom as private, the SDK considers the dictionary private except for device & operatingSystem (which cannot be made private). See privateAttributes for details. (Default: nil)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: isAnonymous
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined isAnonymous for the user. If the client app does not define isAnonymous, the SDK will use the key to set this attribute. isAnonymous cannot be made private. (Default: YES)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: device
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined device for the user. The SDK will determine the device automatically, however the client app can override the value. The SDK will insert the device into the custom dictionary. The device cannot be made private. (Default: the system identified device)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: operatingSystem
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined operatingSystem for the user. The SDK will determine the operatingSystem automatically, however the client app can override the value. The SDK will insert the operatingSystem into the custom dictionary. The operatingSystem cannot be made private. (Default: the system identified operating system)

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: privateAttributes
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Client app defined privateAttributes for the user.

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: init()
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Initializer to create a LDUser. Client configurable attributes are set to their default value. The SDK will automatically set key, device, operatingSystem, and isAnonymous attributes. The SDK embeds device and operatingSystem into the custom dictionary for transmission to LaunchDarkly.

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: init(key:)
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Initializer to create a LDUser with a specific key. Other client configurable attributes are set to their default value. The SDK will automatically set key, device, operatingSystem, and isAnonymous attributes. The SDK embeds device and operatingSystem into the custom dictionary for transmission to LaunchDarkly.

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: init(userDictionary:)
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Initializer that takes a NSDictionary and creates a LDUser from the contents. Uses any keys present to define corresponding attribute values. Initializes attributes not present in the dictionary to their default value. The initializer attempts to set device and operatingSystem from corresponding values embedded in custom. The initializer attempts to set feature flags from values set in config.

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.name: isEqual(object:)
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html#/c:@M@LaunchDark.abstract: Compares users by comparing their user keys only, to allow the client app to collect user information over time

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: mobileKey
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The Mobile key from your LaunchDarkly Account settings (on the left at the bottom). If you have multiple projects be sure to choose the correct Mobile key.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: baseUrl
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The url for making feature flag requests. Do not change unless instructed by LaunchDarkly.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: eventsUrl
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The url for making event reports. Do not change unless instructed by LaunchDarkly.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: streamUrl
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The url for connecting to the clientstream. Do not change unless instructed by LaunchDarkly.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: eventCapacity
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The maximum number of analytics events the LDClient can store. When the LDClient event store reaches the eventCapacity, the SDK discards events until it successfully reports them to LaunchDarkly. (Default: 100)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: connectionTimeout
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The timeout interval for flag requests and event reports. (Default: 10 seconds)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: eventFlushInterval
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The time interval between event reports (Default: 30 seconds)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: flagPollingInterval
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The interval between feature flag requests. Used only for polling mode. (Default: 5 minutes)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: backgroundFlagPollingInterval
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The interval between feature flag requests while running in the background. Used only for polling mode. (Default: 60 minutes)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: minFlagPollingInterval
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The minimum interval between feature flag requests. Used only for polling mode. (5 minutes)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: minBackgroundFlagPollInterval
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The minimum interval between feature flag requests while running in the background. Used only for polling mode. (15 minutes)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: streamingMode
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Controls the method the SDK uses to keep feature flags updated. When set to .streaming, connects to clientstream which notifies the SDK of feature flag changes. When set to .polling, an efficient polling mechanism is used to periodically request feature flag values. Ignored for watchOS, which always uses .polling. See LDStreamingMode for more details. (Default: .streaming)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: enableBackgroundUpdates
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Enables feature flag updates when your app is in the background. Allowed on macOS only. (Default: NO)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: startOnline
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Controls LDClient start behavior. When YES, calling start causes LDClient to go online. When NO, calling start causes LDClient to remain offline. If offline at start, set the client online to receive flag updates. (Default: YES)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: allUserAttributesPrivate
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Treat all user attributes as private for event reporting for all users.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: privateUserAttributes
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: User attributes and top level custom dictionary keys to treat as private for event reporting for all users.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: useReport
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Directs the SDK to use REPORT for HTTP requests to connect to clientstream and make feature flag requests. When NO the SDK uses GET for these requests. Do not use unless advised by LaunchDarkly. (Default: NO)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: inlineUserInEvents
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Controls how the SDK reports the user in analytics event reports. When set to YES, event reports will contain the user attributes, except attributes marked as private. When set to NO, event reports will contain the user’s key only, reducing the size of event reports. (Default: NO)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: debugMode
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Enables logging for debugging. (Default: NO)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: evaluationReasons
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Enables requesting evaluation reasons for all flags. (Default: NO)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: maxCachedUsers
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: An Integer that tells UserEnvironmentFlagCache the maximum number of users to locally cache. Can be set to -1 for unlimited cached users. (Default: 5)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: diagnosticOptOut
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Set to true to opt out of sending diagnostic data. (Default: false)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: diagnosticRecordingInterval
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The interval between sending periodic diagnostic data. (Default: 15 minutes)

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: wrapperName
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: For use by wrapper libraries to set an identifying name for the wrapper being used. This will be sent in the “X-LaunchDarkly-Wrapper” header on requests to the LaunchDarkly servers to allow recording metrics on the usage of these wrapper libraries.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: wrapperVersion
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: For use by wrapper libraries to report the version of the library in use. If the wrapperName has not been set this field will be ignored. Otherwise the verison strill will be included with the wrapperName in the “X-LaunchDarkly-Wrapper” header on requests to the LaunchDarkly servers.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: getSecondaryMobileKeys()
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns a Dictionary of identifying names to unique mobile keys to access secondary environments.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: setSecondaryMobileKeys(_:)
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a Dictionary of identifying names to unique mobile keys to access secondary environments in the LDConfig. Throws if you try to add duplicate keys or put the primary key or name in secondaryMobileKeys.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: init(mobileKey:)
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: LDConfig constructor. Configurable values are all set to their default values. The client app can modify these values as desired. Note that client app developers may prefer to get the LDConfig from LDClient.config (ObjcLDClient.config) in order to retain previously set values.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: isEqual(object:)
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Compares the settable properties in 2 LDConfig structs

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: isOnline
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Reports the online/offline state of the LDClient.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: setOnline(_:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Set the LDClient online/offline.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: setOnline(_:completion:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Set the LDClient online/offline.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: identify(user:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The LDUser set into the LDClient may affect the set of feature flags returned by the LaunchDarkly server, and ties event tracking to the user. See LDUser for details about what information can be retained.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: identify(user:completion:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: The LDUser set into the LDClient may affect the set of feature flags returned by the LaunchDarkly server, and ties event tracking to the user. See LDUser for details about what information can be retained.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: close()
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Stops the LDClient. Stopping the client means the LDClient goes offline and stops recording events. LDClient will no longer provide feature flag values, only returning default values.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: get()
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns an ObjcLDClient wrapper that contains the primary LDClient instance.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: get(environment:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns an LDClient instance for a given environment.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: boolVariation(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns the BOOL variation for the given feature flag. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to a BOOL, or the LDClient is not started, returns the default value.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: boolVariationDetail(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: See boolVariation for more information on variation methods.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: integerVariation(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns the NSInteger variation for the given feature flag. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to a NSInteger, or the LDClient is not started, returns the default value.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: integerVariationDetail(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: See integerVariation for more information on variation methods.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: doubleVariation(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns the double variation for the given feature flag. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to a double, or the LDClient is not started, returns the default value.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: doubleVariationDetail(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: See doubleVariation for more information on variation methods.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: stringVariation(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns the NSString variation for the given feature flag. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to a NSString, or the LDClient is not started, returns the default value, which may be nil.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: stringVariationDetail(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: See stringVariation for more information on variation methods.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: arrayVariation(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns the NSArray variation for the given feature flag. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to a NSArray, or the LDClient is not started, returns the default value, which may be nil..

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: arrayVariationDetail(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: See arrayVariation for more information on variation methods.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: dictionaryVariation(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns the NSDictionary variation for the given feature flag. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to a NSDictionary, or the LDClient is not started, returns the default value, which may be nil..

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: dictionaryVariationDetail(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: See dictionaryVariation for more information on variation methods.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: allFlags
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Returns a dictionary with the flag keys and their values. If the LDClient is not started, returns nil.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeBool(_:owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler for the specified BOOL flag key executed on the specified owner. If the flag’s value changes, executes the handler, passing in the changedFlag containing the old and new flag values. See ObjcLDBoolChangedFlag for details.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeInteger(_:owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler for the specified NSInteger flag key executed on the specified owner. If the flag’s value changes, executes the handler, passing in the changedFlag containing the old and new flag values. See ObjcLDIntegerChangedFlag for details.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeDouble(_:owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler for the specified double flag key executed on the specified owner. If the flag’s value changes, executes the handler, passing in the changedFlag containing the old and new flag values. See ObjcLDDoubleChangedFlag for details.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeString(_:owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler for the specified NSString flag key executed on the specified owner. If the flag’s value changes, executes the handler, passing in the changedFlag containing the old and new flag values. See ObjcLDStringChangedFlag for details.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeArray(_:owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler for the specified NSArray flag key executed on the specified owner. If the flag’s value changes, executes the handler, passing in the changedFlag containing the old and new flag values. See ObjcLDArrayChangedFlag for details.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeDictionary(_:owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler for the specified NSDictionary flag key executed on the specified owner. If the flag’s value changes, executes the handler, passing in the changedFlag containing the old and new flag values. See ObjcLDDictionaryChangedFlag for details.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeKeys(_:owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler for the specified flag keys executed on the specified owner. If any observed flag’s value changes, executes the handler 1 time, passing in a dictionary of containing the old and new flag values. See LDChangedFlag (ObjcLDChangedFlag) for details.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeAllKeys(owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler for all flag keys executed on the specified owner. If any flag’s value changes, executes the handler 1 time, passing in a dictionary of containing the old and new flag values. See LDChangedFlag (ObjcLDChangedFlag) for details.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeFlagsUnchanged(owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler executed when a flag update leaves the flags unchanged from their previous values.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: stopObserving(owner:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Removes all observers for the given owner, including a flagsUnchangedObserver

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: observeError(owner:handler:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Sets a handler executed when an error occurs while processing flag or event responses.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDar.name: ObjcLDChangedFlagCollectionHandler
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDar.abstract: Handler passed to the client app when a NSArray feature flag value changes

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: track(key:data:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Adds a custom event to the LDClient event store. A client app can set a tracking event to allow client customized data analysis. Once an app has called track, the app cannot remove the event from the event store.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: track(key:data:metricValue:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: See (track)[x-source-tag://track] for full documentation.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: flush()
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Tells the SDK to immediately send any currently queued events to LaunchDarkly.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: start(configuration:user:completion:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: Starts the LDClient using the passed in config & user. Call this before requesting feature flag values. The LDClient will not go online until you call this method.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.name: start(configuration:user:startWaitSeconds:completion:)
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html#/c:@M@LaunchDa.abstract: See start for more information on starting the SDK.

Classes/ObjcLDClient.html.name: ObjcLDClient
Classes/ObjcLDClient.html.abstract: The LDClient is the heart of the SDK, providing client apps running iOS, watchOS, macOS, or tvOS access to LaunchDarkly services. This singleton provides the ability to set a configuration (LDConfig) that controls how the LDClient talks to LaunchDarkly servers, and a user (LDUser) that provides finer control on the feature flag values delivered to LDClient. Once the LDClient has started, it connects to LaunchDarkly’s servers to get the feature flag values you set in the Dashboard.

Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html.name: ObjcLDConfig
Classes/ObjcLDConfig.html.abstract: Use LDConfig to configure the LDClient. When initialized, a LDConfig contains the default values which can be changed as needed.

Classes/ObjcLDUser.html.name: ObjcLDUser
Classes/ObjcLDUser.html.abstract: LDUser allows clients to collect information about users in order to refine the feature flag values sent to the SDK. For example, the client app may launch with the SDK defined anonymous user. As the user works with the client app, information may be collected as needed and sent to LaunchDarkly. The client app controls the information collected, which LaunchDarkly does not use except as the client directs to refine feature flags. Client apps should follow Apple’s Privacy Policy when collecting user information.

Classes/ObjcLDChangedFlag.html.name: ObjcLDChangedFlag
Classes/ObjcLDChangedFlag.html.abstract: Collects the elements of a feature flag that changed as a result of a clientstream update or feature flag request. The SDK will pass a typed ObjcLDChangedFlag or a collection of ObjcLDChangedFlags into feature flag observer blocks. This is the base type for the typed ObjcLDChangedFlags passed into observer blocks. The client app will have to convert the ObjcLDChangedFlag into the expected typed ObjcLDChangedFlag type.

Enums/LDStreamingMode.html#/s:12LaunchDa.name: streaming
Enums/LDStreamingMode.html#/s:12LaunchDa.abstract: In streaming mode, the LDClient opens a long-running connection to LaunchDarkly’s streaming server (called clientstream). When a flag value changes on the server, the clientstream notifies the SDK to update the value. Streaming mode is not available on watchOS. On iOS and tvOS, the client app must be running in the foreground to connect to clientstream. On macOS the client app may run in either foreground or background to connect to clientstream. If streaming mode is not available, the SDK reverts to polling mode.

Enums/LDStreamingMode.html#/s:12LaunchDa.name: polling
Enums/LDStreamingMode.html#/s:12LaunchDa.abstract: In polling mode, the LDClient requests feature flags from LaunchDarkly’s app server at regular intervals defined in the LDConfig. When a flag value changes on the server, the LDClient will learn of the change the next time the SDK requests feature flags.

Enums/LDStreamingMode.html.name: LDStreamingMode
Enums/LDStreamingMode.html.abstract: Defines the connection modes available to set into LDClient.

Other%20Types.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly22LD.name: LDFlagValueConvertible
Other%20Types.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly22LD.abstract: Protocol used by the SDK to limit feature flag types to those representable on LaunchDarkly servers. Client app developers should not need to use this protocol. The protocol is public because LDClient.variation(forKey:defaultValue:) and LDClient.variationDetail(forKey:defaultValue:) return a type that conforms to this protocol. See LDFlagValue for types that LaunchDarkly feature flags can take.

Other%20Types.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly9LDF.name: LDFlagKey
Other%20Types.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly9LDF.abstract: The feature flag key is a String. This typealias helps define where the SDK expects the string to be a feature flag key.

Other%20Types.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly14LD.name: LDErrorHandler
Other%20Types.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly14LD.abstract: A closure used to notify an observer owner that an error occurred during feature flag processing.

Connection%20Information.html#/s:12Launc.name: LDConnectionModeChangedHandler
Connection%20Information.html#/s:12Launc.abstract: A closure used to notify an observer owner that the current connection mode has changed.

Structs/LDChangedFlag.html#/s:12LaunchDa.name: key
Structs/LDChangedFlag.html#/s:12LaunchDa.abstract: The key of the changed feature flag

Structs/LDChangedFlag.html#/s:12LaunchDa.name: oldValue
Structs/LDChangedFlag.html#/s:12LaunchDa.abstract: The feature flag’s value before the change. The client app will have to convert the oldValue into the expected type.

Structs/LDChangedFlag.html#/s:12LaunchDa.name: newValue
Structs/LDChangedFlag.html#/s:12LaunchDa.abstract: The feature flag’s value after the change. The client app will have to convert the newValue into the expected type.

Structs/LDChangedFlag.html#/s:12LaunchDa.name: objcChangedFlag
Structs/LDChangedFlag.html#/s:12LaunchDa.abstract: An NSObject wrapper for the Swift LDChangeFlag enum. Intended for use in mixed apps when Swift code needs to pass a LDChangeFlag into an Objective-C method.

Flag%20Change%20Observers.html#/s:12Laun.name: LDObserverOwner
Flag%20Change%20Observers.html#/s:12Laun.abstract: An object can own an observer for as long as the object exists. Swift structs and enums cannot be observer owners.

Structs/LDChangedFlag.html.name: LDChangedFlag
Structs/LDChangedFlag.html.abstract: Collects the elements of a feature flag that changed as a result of a clientstream update or feature flag request. The SDK will pass a LDChangedFlag or a collection of LDChangedFlags into feature flag observer closures. The client app will have to convert the old/newValue into the expected type. See LDClient.observe(key:owner:handler:), LDClient.observe(keys:owner:handler:), and LDClient.observeAll(owner:handler:) for more details.

Flag%20Change%20Observers.html#/s:12Laun.name: LDFlagChangeHandler
Flag%20Change%20Observers.html#/s:12Laun.abstract: A closure used to notify an observer owner of a change to a single feature flag’s value.

Flag%20Change%20Observers.html#/s:12Laun.name: LDFlagCollectionChangeHandler
Flag%20Change%20Observers.html#/s:12Laun.abstract: A closure used to notify an observer owner of a change to the feature flags in a collection of LDChangedFlag.

Flag%20Change%20Observers.html#/s:12Laun.name: LDFlagsUnchangedHandler
Flag%20Change%20Observers.html#/s:12Laun.abstract: A closure used to notify an observer owner that a feature flag request resulted in no changes to any feature flag.

Classes/LDEvaluationDetail.html#/s:12Lau.name: value
Classes/LDEvaluationDetail.html#/s:12Lau.abstract: The value of the flag for the current user.

Classes/LDEvaluationDetail.html#/s:12Lau.name: variationIndex
Classes/LDEvaluationDetail.html#/s:12Lau.abstract: The index of the returned value within the flag’s list of variations, or nil if the default was returned.

Classes/LDEvaluationDetail.html#/s:12Lau.name: reason
Classes/LDEvaluationDetail.html#/s:12Lau.abstract: A structure representing the main factor that influenced the resultant flag evaluation value.

Structs/LDUser/CodingKeys.html#/s:12Laun.name: key
Structs/LDUser/CodingKeys.html#/s:12Laun.abstract: Key names match the corresponding LDUser property

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: privatizableAttributes
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: LDUser attributes that can be marked private.

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: key
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined string that uniquely identifies the user. If the client app does not define a key, the SDK will assign an identifier associated with the anonymous user. The key cannot be made private.

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: secondary
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: The secondary key for the user. See the documentation for more information on it’s use for percentage rollout bucketing.

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: name
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined name for the user. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: firstName
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined first name for the user. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: lastName
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined last name for the user. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: country
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined country for the user. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: ipAddress
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined ipAddress for the user. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: email
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined email address for the user. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: avatar
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined avatar for the user. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: custom
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined dictionary for the user. The client app may declare top level dictionary items as private. If the client app defines custom as private, the SDK considers the dictionary private except for device & operatingSystem (which cannot be made private). See privateAttributes for details. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: isAnonymous
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined isAnonymous for the user. If the client app does not define isAnonymous, the SDK will use the key to set this attribute. isAnonymous cannot be made private. (Default: true)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: device
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined device for the user. The SDK will determine the device automatically, however the client app can override the value. The SDK will insert the device into the custom dictionary. The device cannot be made private. (Default: the system identified device)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: operatingSystem
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined operatingSystem for the user. The SDK will determine the operatingSystem automatically, however the client app can override the value. The SDK will insert the operatingSystem into the custom dictionary. The operatingSystem cannot be made private. (Default: the system identified operating system)

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: privateAttributes
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Client app defined privateAttributes for the user.

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: objcLdUser
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: An NSObject wrapper for the Swift LDUser struct. Intended for use in mixed apps when Swift code needs to pass a user into an Objective-C method.

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: init(key:name:firstName:lastName:country:ipAddress:email:avatar:custom:isAnonymous:device:operatingSystem:privateAttributes:secondary:)
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Initializer to create a LDUser. Client configurable attributes each have an optional parameter to facilitate setting user information into the LDUser. The SDK will automatically set key, device, operatingSystem, and isAnonymous attributes if the client does not provide them. The SDK embeds device and operatingSystem into the custom dictionary for transmission to LaunchDarkly.

Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.name: init(userDictionary:)
Structs/LDUser.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly6LD.abstract: Initializer that takes a [String: Any] and creates a LDUser from the contents. Uses any keys present to define corresponding attribute values. Initializes attributes not present in the dictionary to their default value. Attempts to set device and operatingSystem from corresponding values embedded in custom. Attempts to set feature flags from values set in config.
Compares users by comparing their user keys only, to allow the client app to collect user information over time

Structs/LDConfig/Minima.html#/s:12Launch.name: flagPollingInterval
Structs/LDConfig/Minima.html#/s:12Launch.abstract: The minimum time interval between feature flag requests. Used only for polling mode. (5 minutes)

Structs/LDConfig/Minima.html#/s:12Launch.name: backgroundFlagPollingInterval
Structs/LDConfig/Minima.html#/s:12Launch.abstract: The minimum time interval between feature flag requests while running in the background. Used only for polling mode. (15 minutes)

Structs/LDConfig/Minima.html#/s:12Launch.name: diagnosticRecordingInterval
Structs/LDConfig/Minima.html#/s:12Launch.abstract: The minimum time interval between sending periodic diagnostic data. (5 minutes)

Structs/LDConfig/Constants.html#/s:12Lau.name: primaryEnvironmentName
Structs/LDConfig/Constants.html#/s:12Lau.abstract: The default environment name that must be present in a single or multiple environment configuration

Structs/LDConfig/Minima.html.name: Minima
Structs/LDConfig/Minima.html.abstract: The minimum values allowed to be set into LDConfig.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: mobileKey
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The Mobile key from your LaunchDarkly Account settings (on the left at the bottom). If you have multiple projects be sure to choose the correct Mobile key.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: baseUrl
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The url for making feature flag requests. Do not change unless instructed by LaunchDarkly.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: eventsUrl
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The url for making event reports. Do not change unless instructed by LaunchDarkly.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: streamUrl
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The url for connecting to the clientstream. Do not change unless instructed by LaunchDarkly.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: eventCapacity
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The maximum number of analytics events the LDClient can store. When the LDClient event store reaches the eventCapacity, the SDK discards events until it successfully reports them to LaunchDarkly. (Default: 100)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: connectionTimeout
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The timeout interval for flag requests and event reports. (Default: 10 seconds)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: eventFlushInterval
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The time interval between event reports (Default: 30 seconds)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: flagPollingInterval
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The time interval between feature flag requests. Used only for polling mode. (Default: 5 minutes)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: backgroundFlagPollingInterval
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The time interval between feature flag requests while running in the background. Used only for polling mode. (Default: 60 minutes)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: streamingMode
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Controls the method the SDK uses to keep feature flags updated. When set to .streaming, connects to clientstream which notifies the SDK of feature flag changes. When set to .polling, an efficient polling mechanism is used to periodically request feature flag values. Ignored for watchOS, which always uses .polling. See LDStreamingMode for more details. (Default: .streaming)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: enableBackgroundUpdates
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Enables feature flag updates when your app is in the background. Allowed on macOS only. (Default: false)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: startOnline
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Controls LDClient start behavior. When true, calling start causes LDClient to go online. When false, calling start causes LDClient to remain offline. If offline at start, set the client online to receive flag updates. (Default: true)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: allUserAttributesPrivate
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Treat all user attributes as private for event reporting for all users.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: privateUserAttributes
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: User attributes and top level custom dictionary keys to treat as private for event reporting for all users.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: useReport
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Directs the SDK to use REPORT for HTTP requests to connect to clientstream and make feature flag requests. When false the SDK uses GET for these requests. Do not use unless advised by LaunchDarkly. (Default: false)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: inlineUserInEvents
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Controls how the SDK reports the user in analytics event reports. When set to true, event reports will contain the user attributes, except attributes marked as private. When set to false, event reports will contain the user’s key only, reducing the size of event reports. (Default: false)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: isDebugMode
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Enables logging for debugging. (Default: false)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: evaluationReasons
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Enables requesting evaluation reasons for all flags. (Default: false)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: maxCachedUsers
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: An Integer that tells UserEnvironmentFlagCache the maximum number of users to locally cache. Can be set to -1 for unlimited cached users.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: diagnosticOptOut
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Set to true to opt out of sending diagnostic data. (Default: false)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: diagnosticRecordingInterval
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The interval between sending periodic diagnostic data. (Default: 15 minutes)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: wrapperName
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: For use by wrapper libraries to set an identifying name for the wrapper being used. This will be sent in the “X-LaunchDarkly-Wrapper” header on requests to the LaunchDarkly servers to allow recording metrics on the usage of wrapper libraries. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: wrapperVersion
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: For use by wrapper libraries to report the version of the library in use. If the wrapperName has not been set this field will be ignored. Otherwise the version string will be included with the wrapperName in the “X-LaunchDarkly-Wrapper” header on requests to the LaunchDarkly servers. (Default: nil)

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: additionalHeaders
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Additional headers that should be added to all HTTP requests from SDK components to LaunchDarkly services

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: minima
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: LaunchDarkly defined minima for selected configurable items

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: objcLdConfig
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: An NSObject wrapper for the Swift LDConfig struct. Intended for use in mixed apps when Swift code needs to pass a config into an Objective-C method.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: setSecondaryMobileKeys(_:)
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Sets a Dictionary of identifying names to unique mobile keys to access secondary environments in the LDConfig. Throws LDInvalidArgumentError if you try to add duplicate keys or put the primary key or name in secondaryMobileKeys.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: getSecondaryMobileKeys()
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Returns a Dictionary of identifying names to unique mobile keys to access secondary environments.

Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: init(mobileKey:)
Structs/LDConfig.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: LDConfig constructor. Configurable values are all set to their default values. The client app can modify these values as desired. Note that client app developers may prefer to get the LDConfig from LDClient.config in order to retain previously set values.
Compares the settable properties in 2 LDConfig structs

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: isOnline
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Reports the online/offline state of the LDClient.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: setOnline(_:completion:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Set the LDClient online/offline.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: getConnectionInformation()
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Returns an object containing information about successful and/or failed polling or streaming connections to LaunchDarkly

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: close()
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Stops the LDClient. Stopping the client means the LDClient goes offline and stops recording events. LDClient will no longer provide feature flag values, only returning default values.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: identify(user:completion:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: The LDUser set into the LDClient may affect the set of feature flags returned by the LaunchDarkly server, and ties event tracking to the user. See LDUser for details about what information can be retained.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: variation(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Returns the variation for the given feature flag. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to the correct return type, or the LDClient is not started, returns the default value. Use this method when the default value is a non-Optional type. See variation with the Optional return value when the default value can be nil.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: variationDetail(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Returns the LDEvaluationDetail for the given feature flag. LDEvaluationDetail gives you more insight into why your variation contains the specified value. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to the correct return type, or the LDClient is not started, returns an LDEvaluationDetail with the default value. Use this method when the default value is a non-Optional type. See variationDetail with the Optional return value when the default value can be nil. See variationWithdefaultValue

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: variation(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Returns the variation for the given feature flag. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to the correct return type, or the LDClient is not started, returns the default value, which may be nil. Use this method when the default value is an Optional type. See variation with the non-Optional return value when the default value cannot be nil.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: variationDetail(forKey:defaultValue:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Returns the LDEvaluationDetail for the given feature flag. LDEvaluationDetail gives you more insight into why your variation contains the specified value. If the flag does not exist, cannot be cast to the correct return type, or the LDClient is not started, returns an LDEvaluationDetail with the default value, which may be nil. Use this method when the default value is a Optional type. See variationWithoutdefaultValue

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: allFlags
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Returns a dictionary with the flag keys and their values. If the LDClient is not started, returns nil.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: observe(key:owner:handler:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Sets a handler for the specified flag key executed on the specified owner. If the flag’s value changes, executes the handler, passing in the changedFlag containing the old and new flag values. See LDChangedFlag for details.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: observe(keys:owner:handler:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Sets a handler for the specified flag keys executed on the specified owner. If any observed flag’s value changes, executes the handler 1 time, passing in a dictionary of [LDFlagKey: LDChangedFlag] containing the old and new flag values. See LDChangedFlag for details.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: observeAll(owner:handler:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Sets a handler for all flag keys executed on the specified owner. If any flag’s value changes, executes the handler 1 time, passing in a dictionary of [LDFlagKey: LDChangedFlag] containing the old and new flag values. See LDChangedFlag for details.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: observeFlagsUnchanged(owner:handler:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Sets a handler executed when a flag update leaves the flags unchanged from their previous values.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: observeCurrentConnectionMode(owner:handler:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Sets a handler executed when ConnectionInformation.currentConnectionMode changes.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: stopObserving(owner:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Removes all observers for the given owner, including the flagsUnchangedObserver

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: observeError(owner:handler:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Undocumented

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: track(key:data:metricValue:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Adds a custom event to the LDClient event store. A client app can set a tracking event to allow client customized data analysis. Once an app has called track, the app cannot remove the event from the event store.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: flush()
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Tells the SDK to immediately send any currently queued events to LaunchDarkly.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: start(config:user:completion:)
Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.abstract: Starts the LDClient using the passed in config & user. Call this before requesting feature flag values. The LDClient will not go online until you call this method.

Classes/LDClient.html#/s:12LaunchDarkly8.name: start(config:user:startWaitSeconds:completion:)

Classes/LDClient.html.name: LDClient
Classes/LDClient.html.abstract: The LDClient is the heart of the SDK, providing client apps running iOS, watchOS, macOS, or tvOS access to LaunchDarkly services. This singleton provides the ability to set a configuration (LDConfig) that controls how the LDClient talks to LaunchDarkly servers, and a user (LDUser) that provides finer control on the feature flag values delivered to LDClient. Once the LDClient has started, it connects to LaunchDarkly’s servers to get the feature flag values you set in the Dashboard.

Structs/LDConfig.html.name: LDConfig
Structs/LDConfig.html.abstract: Use LDConfig to configure the LDClient. When initialized, a LDConfig contains the default values which can be changed as needed.

Structs/LDUser.html.name: LDUser
Structs/LDUser.html.abstract: LDUser allows clients to collect information about users in order to refine the feature flag values sent to the SDK. For example, the client app may launch with the SDK defined anonymous user. As the user works with the client app, information may be collected as needed and sent to LaunchDarkly. The client app controls the information collected, which LaunchDarkly does not use except as the client directs to refine feature flags. Client apps should follow Apple’s Privacy Policy when collecting user information.
